parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty front wheel bearings and races can cause vibration, noise, and premature tire wear, which can lead to accidents or reduced vehicle stability.
Broken rear U-bolts can cause loss of control, accidents, or reduced vehicle stability.
Premature tire wear can cause reduced traction, accidents, or reduced vehicle stability.
Front axle problems can cause loss of control, accidents, or reduced vehicle stability.
Repeated alternator failure can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to stalling, battery drain, and potential safety risks.
Cracked windows can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks and reduced visibility.
Malfunctioning dashboard components can cause distractions, reduce visibility, and lead to accidents.
Faulty wiring harnesses can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to safety risks, stalling, and reduced vehicle performance.
Electrical panel shorts can cause fires, damage to electrical components, and safety risks.
The failure of the steering shaft U-joint can cause a loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering shaft sector of the U-joint locks up
causing difficulty or inability to steer the vehicle.
